				Electrolyte balance is very important for proper functioning of the whole organism. When the electrolyte balance
				is disturbed, muscle and nervous system malfunctions (cramps) or excessive water retention can occur.
				Electrolyte replenishment is especially important during intense physical activity when electrolyte balance is
				compromised. This dietary supplement provides the optimal solution to quickly and effectively replenish all 6
				electrolytes: magnesium, sodium, potassium, calcium, phosphorus and chloride.
			</p>
			<p>
				Electrolytes are small charged dissolved particles known as ions that conduct electric current in liquid
				solutions and perform many tasks in the human body. The adult body is approximately 60% water, which means that
				almost every fluid and cell in the body contains electrolytes. Electrolytes help the body regulate chemical
				reactions, maintain the balance between the fluids inside and outside the cells and, most importantly, are used
				by the cells in the body to conduct electrical charges that make it possible, for example, to contract muscles.
			</p>
			<p>
				Amino acids fall into two main categories: essential and non-essential. Essential amino acids are amino acids
				that the human body cannot make itself, which means they must be taken from food or supplements. Non-essential
				amino acids are amino acids the human body can produce under certain conditions. However, semi-essential amino
				acids are also mentioned here. This is a special term for some non-essential amino acids (such as histidine)
				that the body can make, but in some cases their production is insufficient. Inadequate production of these amino
				acids can occur, for example, during illness or severe physical strain.
			</p>
